13 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 54-35 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Facility construction committee - Powers and duties.
16 1. The legislative management, during each biennium, shall appoint a facility
17 construction committee in the same manner as the legislative management appoints
18 other interim committees. The legislative management shall appoint seven members
19 of the house of representatives, at least one of whom must represent the minority
20 faction of the house of representatives, and six members of the senate, at least one of
21 whom must represent the minority faction of the senate, to the committee.
22 Appointment to the committee is for a term of two years at the discretion of the
23 legislative management. The legislative management shall designate the chairman of
24 the committee. The committee shall operate according to the statutes and procedure
25 governing the operation of other legislative management interim committees.
26 2. The committee shall study and review construction projects impacting facilities,
27 including owned and leased facilities, from which the state operates, excluding
28 facilities operated by entities under the control of the state board of higher education,
29 for the purpose of:
30 a. Ensuring efficient and effective use of state resources in compliance with law and
31 legislative intent;
