1 b. Providing the legislative assembly with formal, objective information regarding
2 state facilities and facility construction projects for the basis of legislative action;
3 and
4 c. Providing legislative input to state agencies regarding any proposal for a new,
5 expanded, or renovated facility.
6 3. A state agency, excluding entities under the control of the state board of higher
7 education, shall inform the legislative council prior to issuing an invitation for architect,
8 engineer, construction management, or land surveying services under section
9 54 - 44.7 - 03 for the purpose of constructing a new facility or a renovation or addition to
10 an existing facility.
11 4. A state agency, excluding entities under the control of the state board of higher
12 education, shall inform the legislative council prior to entering into any agreement for
13 the construction or renovation of a facility leased or to be leased by the state agency.
14 5. The committee may call on personnel from state agencies to furnish such information
15 as the committee may request.
16 6. The committee may advise the director of the office of management and budget and
17 state agencies on matters relating to location, design, and estimated costs for facility
18 construction and renovation projects.
19 7. The committee shall meet at least once each calendar quarter upon the call of the
20 chairman.
21 8. The committee shall report the findings and recommendations of the committee to the
22 capitol grounds planning commission regarding its review of the construction of a new
23 facility or renovation or addition to an existing facility located on the capitol grounds.
24 9. The committee shall report the findings and recommendations of the committee, along
25 with any necessary legislation, to the legislative management and to the legislative
26 assembly.
